Peer enumeration for Ableton Link.

Exposes the per-session peer list (already maintained internally by
Link) via a public method on the controller and BasicLink. Each entry
carries the peer's NodeState (NodeId, SessionId, Timeline, etc.) plus
the local gateway IP it was discovered on and its measurement/audio
endpoints.

Used by SuperClock::listPeers / OSC `/link/peers/get` for diagnostic
visibility into who's in our Link session and which IPs they came
from.

Two-file patch:
  - include/ableton/link/Controller.hpp  (add Controller::sessionPeers)
  - include/ableton/Link.hpp             (add BasicLink::sessionPeers)

Wire protocol unchanged. No existing API behaviour changes. Public
surface gains one read-only method; existing callers unaffected.

Pinned to Link-4.0.

--- a/include/ableton/link/Controller.hpp
+++ b/include/ableton/link/Controller.hpp
@@ -198,6 +198,15 @@

   std::size_t numPeers() const { return mSessionPeerCounter.mSessionPeerCount; }

+  // SUPERSONIC PATCH: expose the set of peers in our current session,
+  // including each peer's gateway IP (the local interface they were
+  // discovered on) and their NodeState/measurement/audio endpoints.
+  // Returned by value so the caller owns a stable snapshot. Not RT-safe.
+  std::vector<std::pair<PeerState, discovery::IpAddress>> sessionPeers() const
+  {
+    return mPeers.sessionPeers(mSessionId);
+  }
+
   // Get the current Link client state. Thread-safe but may block, so
   // it cannot be used from audio thread.
   ClientState clientState() const { return mClientState.get(); }
--- a/include/ableton/Link.hpp
+++ b/include/ableton/Link.hpp
@@ -119,6 +119,18 @@
    *  Realtime-safe: yes
